The paper deals with complexity measures for randomized query complexity, which is a topic in computational complexity theory. The paper specifically focuses on certificate complexity, expectational certificate complexity, and fractional certificate complexity, which are all related to communication complexity and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses distributed query complexity, which falls under the category of distributed systems (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper involves analyzing Boolean functions, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper uses techniques from learning theory (cs.LG) to prove some of its results.
